<p>Friday 27th July 1917</p>
<p>2 or 3 Fritz planes came over dropped bombs all round and missed us.<br/>Guard woke me up at 5am, fed mules and put harness on, then had breakfast. Left camp at 6am and reported to the 12th battery about 6.10am.[several lines cannot be transcribed as they have been written over]<br/>was in charge of us has no pass for our team, to proceed to the gun position. Day finish 7.30pm. Just heard that Doug Reynolds killed, Bishop wounded.</p>
